This project is a java based translator from GDLII(Game Description Language with Incomplete Information) to MCK(Model Checking of Knowledge)

To run the translator, first make sure you have java and ant installed then from the root folder type
$ ant jar
$ java -jar deploy/MckTranslator -i path/to/file.gdl -o path/to/output.mck --use-prover
 
To run unit tests enter
$ ant test
then a test mck file is saved in build-test/mck-translation.mck

To run the generated mck file
$ mck path/to/file.mck

You can edit specification definitions in the section labeled "--Specifications" of the generated mck file.
